>data_prog openoutside~
Passage beyond this narrow ledge is blocked by a massive wall of granite
blocks.  The top of the wall is crenellated, and guards can be occasionally
glimpsed as they patrol above.  Along the bottom of the wall, defensive
runes and wards are set in the stone.  The ledge extends northward and
southward, but so does the wall.  The only passage through the wall is at
this point, through the well-guarded gatehouse.  The angular peak of the
Fortress of the Eye is visible beyond the wall, with the stylized crystal
window at the tip resembling an open eye.  To the east, a deep ravine is
spanned by a slender stone bridge. 
    
The gatehouse is open, and the courtyard beyond it visible.
~
