USE OF THE SCALE OF ORLIN

The Knight Lord is given charge to care for and instruct Knights in the use
of the Scale of Orlin.  The Scale of Orlin is a complex instrument, only
understood by those dedicated to Enaerai and in the knight order.  It
measures the balance between good and evil, between law and chaos, and
between the strength of the houses.  It gives priority to the measure in
that order, as should the Knights.  The scale is used in the following
manner:

consult scale 

~
E
eight~
NAMING A RENEGADE KNIGHT

Only the Knight Lord may declare a Knight to be renegade and oathbreaker. 
Normally, Knights accused of oathbreaking are given warning and an
opportunity to defend themselves (in a simple court, as directed by the
Lord).  The naming of renegade is a last resort, to declare to the Knight
that their mortal life, which is sworn to Enaerai, is forfeit.  When a
Knight is judged to be renegade, and is present in the realm, the Knight
Lord uses the oathstone in the following manner: 

renegade <name>

~
E
seven~
DEMOTING AN OFFICER OF THE KNIGHTS

For whatever reason, if a leader among the Knights is to be demoted or
returned to standard Knight status, the administrator, before the oath
stone, asks the Knight whether they accept the removal of office.  The
Knight must respond \#I accept\# (and should be so informed), and then the
administrator binds the act through use of the oath stone, as follows:

oath knight <name> 

~
E
six~
ADMINISTERING THE LORD OATH

At least two Knight Captains must agree on the candidate for the Knight
Lord position, and the prospective Knight Lord given the oath by another
Captain, for the oath ceremony and granting of rank to be considered 
valid before Enaerai.

As with the other oath ceremonies, the candidate stands in the gold ring,
before a Knight Captain.  The candidate is formally charged with directing
the Knighthood and taking responsibility for the balance of Avendar before
Enaerai.  The Captain then questions: \#Will you accept this charge?\# 
The candidate must respond \#I will\# (and should be informed beforehand that
those are the necessary words to be uttered, for the oath stone to bind the
ceremony).

This done, the administrator of the oath uses the oath stone in the
following manner:

oath lord <name>
~
E
five~
ADMINISTERING THE CAPTAIN OATH

Traditionally, the candidate for the captaincy stands in the gold ring
before the Knight Lord (or another Captain, in the Lord\@s absence).  The
candidate is formally charged with directing and upholding the work of the
division they are to direct.  The administrator then questions: \#Will you
pledge to faithfully serve Enaerai and the balance as Knight Captain?\#  The
candidate must respond \#I will\# (and should be informed beforehand that
those are the requisite ceremonial words that must be uttered, for the oath
stone to bind the ceremony).  

This done, the administrator of the oath uses the oath stone in the
following manner: 

oath captain <name> 

~
E
four~
ADMINISTERING THE KNIGHT OATH

The worthy applicant traditionally stands in the gold ring before the Knight
Lord (or Captain, in the Lord\@s absence).  The applicant is questioned
regarding their desire to take the oath, whether it is done of their own
volition, and whether they understand the consequenses of breaking the oath.


If the applicant gives satisfactory answers, the adminstrator of the oath
questions: \#Will you take the oath upon yourself now?\#  The applicant must
respond \#I will\# (and should be informed beforehand that those are the
proper ceremonial words, without which the oath stone will not bind the
oath).  

This done, the administrator of the oath uses the oath stone in the
following manner: 

oath knight <name>

~
E
three~
THE KNIGHT GUARD

In the temple of Enaerai, a Knight stands guard at the doors of the
compound.  He will permit only Knights to pass the doors, and those the
Knights wish to invite within the compound.  If Knights wish to invite
someone into the compound, they may say the following: 

escort <name>

The guard will alert all Knights when others attempt to force their way into
the compound, and will also attack renegades of the Knighthood on sight.  
~
