#22087
A Mountain Glade~
Along this stretch of the small mountain trail, the slopes widens into a
tiny valley nestled between two mountain ridges.  In the valley stand a
glade of tall straight evergreens and a few stout hardwoods.  The trail is
covered in dry brown needles, and the thin air is pungent with the scent of
the pines.  Throughout the valley are several stumps and a few small piles
of woodchips.  
